QOUTE:<br>
Imagine, what could Shintou of done in the Temple of Cazic Thule had their not been Dante there, Powerleveling the Bard.<br>
<br>
Maybe he would of faught and trained fighting the Lizards.<br>
Maybe he could of called some of his Friends and Guild Brothers and Sisters and went Adventuring within the Temple.<br>
Or Maybe he could of just been bored and left the Temple, seeking another place to train his skills<br>
<br>
END QOUTE<br>
<br>
Would this not have been the same thing had thier been a role playing group at the Temple? Your ability to do these things you mention has NOTHING to do with role playing.<br>
You inability to do these things has EVERYTHING to do with mob spawn issues.<br>
<br>
1. Nothing preventing you from going elsewhere in CT and fighting lizards.<br>
2. Nothing preventing you from calling some friends/guildies to CT to fight besides the Temple in CT.<br>
<br>
 Some one was in a mob spawn spot you wanted, this has NOTHING to do with role playing. Your blaming your &quot;inability&quot; to do certain things on lack of role playing is bull honkey doodoo. You got upset cause someone was in a spot you wanted, and since they were &quot;not-roleplayers&quot; you find an easy venue to vent your frustation. I do understand your concern with lack of role playing response to your role playing statements to the 2 people at CT Temple, but they did not affect your ability to continue on and enjoy the game.  <br>
<br>
I will give you a REAL example of powergaming affecting someone in EQ: My second char on another server was at this same exact spot. A full group of level 26-30ish chars in the Temple. We were there for hours having fun when long comes a single 50+ necro and proceeds to steal the camp from us, killing the Tae before we can, etc. He wanted to twink his rogue, imagine that. <br>
<br>
Welcome to EQ Ronin,  the nature of mob spawn issues.  Nothing role play about it brother, boils down like this for all of us. Thankfully, there is for the most part a nice set of people on FV. Really be sad to see the bickering and fighting that goes on over mob spawns on other servers come to FV. Please stop blaming mob spawn issues on role-playing, has zero to do with role playing. <br>
